# No Purple/Blue as Primary Color

Do not use purple or blue gradients or colors as the primary color in the design.

## Avoid

- Purple (`#7c3aed`, `#8b5cf6`, `purple-500`, etc.) as the main brand/accent color
- Blue (`#3b82f6`, `#2563eb`, `blue-500`, etc.) as the main brand/accent color
- Purple-to-blue or blue-to-purple gradients as the dominant visual element

## Prefer Instead

- Warm accents: amber, orange, coral, rose, terracotta
- Cool alternatives: teal, emerald, cyan (distinct from generic blue)
- Neutral-dominant palettes with a non-purple/blue accent
- Bold or unexpected choices: chartreuse, burnt sienna, deep green

## Examples

```css
/* ❌ Avoid */
.primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7c3aed, #3b82f6); }
.accent { color: #8b5cf6; }

/* ✅ Prefer */
.primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d9488, #059669); }
.accent { color: #ea580c; }
```
